1/ AWS Inbound Config
  => Add HTTP and HTTPS in Inbound Rule
  
2/ Install NodeJS

sudo apt install build-essential

=> Test: node hello.js (https://www.songonha.com/2022/12/how-to-set-up-a-node-js-application-for-production-on-ubuntu-18-04.html)
      
3/ Install Nginx
  ==> Configuration
  sudo systemctl status nginx => running
  
  Edit => sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/54.169.30.19
  server {
        listen 80;
        listen [::]:80;

        root /var/www/54.169.30.19/html;
        index index.html index.htm index.nginx-debian.html;

        server_name 54.169.30.19;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:3000;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
    }
}
   Unnote => Block Transfer
   sudo nano /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
  
   ...
   http {
      ...
      server_names_hash_bucket_size 64;
      ...
   }
   ...
   
   
   Edit line 5 at index.js:
   port 9091 ==> 3000 (the same with port in location of nginx)
   
   node index.js
   
   All done!!! Yeah!!!!
